mediaNotes:
This individual is largely singing Field Sparrow-like Group B song type, a tonal song, more typically delivered at dawn.  At 09:54, this bird switches from Group B to a single Group A buzzy song more commonly heard during the day time.  A second S. discolor is heard singing Group B song in the background.  The delivery of Group B songs from the primary subject and the second individual in the background would seem indicate an aggressive interaction between individuals--G. Budney, 2Sep2015.
